text: Bethany Zummo is an American volleyball player. She played at the 2016 Summer Paralympics, winning a gold medal, and 2019 Parapan American Games. She studied at Dublin High School. She played for University of Central Oklahoma. In 2020, she sewed masks and donated them. == References == Category:Living people Category:American sitting volleyball players Category:1993 births Category:Paralympic gold medalists for the United States
